        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Hagerstown</placeName>
                <date>April 16/63</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I take the liberty to address<lb/> to you these few lines to inform
                in regard to<lb/> the proceedings of a certain gentleman named<lb/> “<persName>Rabbi
                    Holstein</persName>” whom you gave a good<lb/>
                <sic>reccomendation</sic> as a man who would &amp; could<lb/> with integrity fill
                the office of a Schoet &amp;<lb/> Hassan, but I am sorry to say you were
                greatly<lb/> mistaken in your man as you will hear from<lb/> the following facts
                which I hope you will place<lb/> in a <sic>conspicous</sic> part of your much
                valuable<lb/> Paper, the “Occident” for it is a disgrace to the<lb/> Jewish name.
                    <persName>Mr Holstein</persName> came here last<lb/>
                <date>January</date> with his family with letters of<lb/>
                <sic>reccomendation</sic> from <persName>Rev Dr Raphel</persName> of
                    <placeName>New<lb/> York</placeName> &amp; <persName>Rev I. Leeser</persName> of
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> as a<lb/> man capable to instruct the
                children of<lb/> this town in various forms &amp; rites of the<lb/> Jewish Religion
                &amp; also to butcher for the<lb/> Jewish families of this town so that could<lb/>
                live like true Israelites, but the disgraced his<lb/> office in the following
                manner. First he<lb/> persuaded a certain man here a butcher &amp; a<lb/>
                <persName>Jehuda</persName> to leave his wife &amp; children, &amp; at last<lb/> had
                so much power over this man that he</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>left his wife &amp; children to want &amp; he (<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Holstein</persName>) went in partnership with<lb/> this butcher &amp;
                did not send to his business<lb/> at all for which he came for. He did not<lb/>
                teach the children would not butcher as a (Schoet)<lb/> ought to have done) for an
                Israelite; also on a<lb/>
                <date>Sabbath</date> he smoked, butchered became beastly<lb/> drunk, &amp; tried
                more than once to drive the<lb/> poor woman (whom he had ruined already by<lb/>
                depriving the mother of a husband &amp; the<lb/> children of a father) in the street
                &amp; insulting<lb/> her in every manner possible that he made himself<lb/> so
                obnoxious that the children of this town<lb/> both Jews &amp; Christians stare at
                him when they<lb/> saw him <persName>Mrs Stein</persName> the forsaken woman
                with<lb/> her children moved in a house which was<lb/> bought by her husband &amp;
                    <persName>Mr Holstein</persName> bought<lb/> the house from her husband so that
                he<lb/> could drive the poor suffering soul out into<lb/> the street but he did not
                succeed as well as he<lb/> expected for by breaking the peace so often &amp;c<lb/>
                the law was on her side &amp; at last he was<lb/> arrested with <persName>Mr
                    Stein</persName> &amp; placed in jail where<lb/> thanks be to the Almighty he
                will stay there<lb/> but in my opinion he ought to rot there his<lb/> lifetime.
                Being advised by the leading<lb/> Israelites to write the above facts so that
                the<lb/> whole world should know it &amp; so take caution<lb/> Hoping that you will
                correct all mistakes</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>and send me the “Occident” in which you will<lb/> place it I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your obedient Serv't</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Jacob J. Greenewald</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Son of <persName>Mr Greeenewald</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">of the firm <persName>Greenewald &amp;<lb/>Kohlberg</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <placeName>No 110 N. Third</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Please excuse</p>
            <p>mistakes &amp; bad writing</p>
            <p>N. B. Give the above to <persName>Dr Wise</persName> of
                        <placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic></placeName><lb/> so that he can place in
                public print<lb/> Yours <persName role="author">JJG</persName>.</p>
        </body>
